  "prompt": "Where is travencore state in India?",
  "response": "Travancore was a princely state located on the southwestern coast of India, primarily in the region that is now the state of Kerala. It was a significant territory that existed until 1949, when it merged with the neighboring state of Cochin to form the Travancore-Cochin state. Today, the area that once comprised Travancore is part of the modern state of Kerala, bordered by the Arabian Sea to the west and the Western Ghats to the east. The capital of Travancore was Thiruvananthapuram, which is now the capital of Kerala.",
